This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of patches in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of non-local information in the pre-processing step suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
